Evraz Highveld Paid Former CEO Ballandino $3.6 Million For Two Months Work

-- B y   C a r l i   L o u r e n s
-- 
2011-04-05T08:13:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-05/evraz-highveld-paid-former-ceo-ballandino-3-6-million-for-two-months-work.html
Evraz Highveld Steel & Vanadium
Ltd., the South African unit of  Russia ’s  Evraz Group SA (EVR) , paid
former Chief Executive Officer Walter Ballandino 24 million rand
($3.6 million) including termination pay last year, of which he
worked two months before resigning.  Ballandino, who headed up eMalahleni, South Africa-based
Evraz Highveld since July 2007, resigned with effect from Feb.
28, 2010, the company said last year. He was paid 17.5 million
rand in 2009, according to the company’s 2010  annual report .  The steelmaker on March 16 reported a loss before interest,
tax, depreciation and amortization of 263 million rand for the
12 months to Dec. 31, compared with earnings of 447 million rand
a year earlier. Shares in the company fell 25 percent to 69.05
rand in Johannesburg the following day, and traded at 70.60 rand
as of 9:41 a.m. local time today, giving a decline of 15 percent
since the start of the year.  Scott MacDonald , who replaced Balladino, resigned with
effect from April 11, the company said in a separate statement
today. Non-executive director Dmitrij Scuka will serve as acting
CEO until a permanent appointment is made, the Evraz unit said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Carli Lourens in Johannesburg at 
